<div class="section">Welcome to Ninf Home Page</div>

<div class="abstract">
The Ninf Project is developing Grid technologies which allows users to
access various resources such as hardware, software and scientific
data on the Grid with an easy-to-use interface.  The Ninf system is a
<a href="http://www.eece.unm.edu/~apm/docs/APM_GridRPC_0702.pdf">Grid
RPC</a> system which has been developed by the Ninf Project.
Ninf system provides Ninf Remote Procedure Call facilities which
is designed to provide a programmming interface similar to
conventional function calls and enable the user to build Grid-enabled
applications.
<br>
</div>
<br>
<div class="section"> <img align="middle" src="image/Lecture.gif" width="20"> About Ninf-G </div>
<strong>
<div class="section_contents">
Ninf-G is a reference implementation of Grid RPC system using the <a
href="http://www.globus.org/">Globus Toolkit</a>.  Ninf-G provides
Grid RPC APIs which are discussed for the standardization at the <a
href="http://www.eece.unm.edu/~apm/">Advanced Programming Models
Research Group</a> of the <a
href="http://www.globalgridforum.org/">Global Grid Forum</a>.  The
details of the standardization of the Grid RPC APIs is reported on the
<a href="http://www.eece.unm.edu/~apm/docs/APM_GridRPC_0702.pdf"> GGF
Working Group Document</a>.<br>
</div>
